flavor_text_entries.gold:
Its tail is so
powerful that it
can use it to grab a tree branch and
hold itself up in
the air.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
It lives atop tall
trees. When leap­
ing from branch to branch, it
deftly uses its
tail for balance.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
It uses its tail
to hang on to tree
branches. It uses its momentum to
swing from one
branch to another.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
AIPOM’s tail ends in a hand-like
appendage that can be cleverly
manipulated. However, because the POKéMON uses its
tail so much, its real hands have become
rather clumsy.

flavor_text_entries.emerald:

appendage. However, because it uses the
tail so much, AIPOM’s real hands have
become rather clumsy.

flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It uses its tail to pluck fruits
that are out of reach. Its tail is
more adept than its real hands.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
It lives atop giant trees.
It wraps its tail around a branch
so it won’t fall off while asleep.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
It lives high among the treetops.
It can use its tail as freely and
cleverly as its hands.

flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
As it did more and more with its tail, its hands
became clumsy. It makes its nest high in
the treetops.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
It searches for prey from the tops of trees.
When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet,
Aipom gets excited and pounces.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand.
Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
